# Backend Python

## Layout

- Routes: `backend/app/api/routes/`
- Schemas: `backend/app/schemas/`
- Services: `backend/app/services/`
- Director: `backend/app/director/`
- Config: `backend/app/core/config.py` (Pydantic Settings) — no hardcoded hosts/ports

## Tests

- Location: `backend/tests/`
- Runner: `make test-backend` or `backend/run-tests.sh`
- Autouse fixtures in `backend/tests/conftest.py` set `OSC_DRY_RUN=true`, patch data dirs, reset signal trace
- Never set `OSC_DRY_RUN=false` without explicit fake receivers (`backend/app/director/testing/fake_osc_receiver.py`)

## Lint

```bash
cd backend && ruff check app tests
```

Line length: 100 (py311).

## Director outputs

When adding or changing output paths (OSC, MIDI, TCP):

- Emit signal-trace events via `backend/app/director/outputs/signal_trace.py`
- Add/update tests: `test_signal_trace.py`, `test_osc_queue_trace.py`, `test_run_epoch_queue.py`

## Imports from scripts

Scripts under `backend/scripts/` import from `app.*` with `PYTHONPATH=.` (set by run-tests.sh / run-native.sh).
